You are given an integer $n$.  You need to determine the minimum number of ice cream balls you need to buy to be able to make $n$ different types of ice cream.  Each ice cream is made with two balls, and two ice creams are different if they have different sets of ball flavors.  You can use the same flavor for both balls in an ice cream. 

For example, if $n=3$, you could make the following ice creams:

* {1, 2}
* {1, 3}
* {2, 3}



You need at least two balls of the same flavor to make an ice cream with that flavor.
